name: Book of Kells Alphabet Pictures
description:
This hand embroidered Celtic Bird is inspired by the exquisite illustrated letters in "The Book of Kells".  

 
This exquisite bird is hand embroidered with beads and sequins and depicts the Celtic letter O. 

It is embroidered on blue velvet. 

 
The picture frame measures 8.5 inches height x 8.5 inches width.

name: The Book of Kells Alphabet Keyrings
description:
Free Shipping Worldwide

Our hand embroidered Book of Kells alphabet keyrings are inspired by the ornate zoomorphic lettering in The Book of Kells.

This letter depicts the Celtic letter A.

name: Irish Castles - Dig & Discover
description:
Dig out a little castle, made of soft plaster, to find your hidden treasure.

The Digging tools are provided.

The treasure you will find buried inside this castle is one of the four National Treasures of Ireland pendants:

The Lismore Crosier,

A Celtic Lunula,

The Cross of Cong,

The Salamandar.      
 
 
Each pendant comes with an adjustable black cord strap.

name: Irish Posters
description:
Free Shipping Worldwide

My handmade Celtic posters are printed on tea stained hand-made paper.  

The Desiderata.  

The Desiderata is a 1927 prose poem by American writer Max Ehrmann (1872-1945). 

Hand crafted wooden poles adorn the top and the bottom of 
the poster.  They are ready to hang.

Each poster measures approx. 13 inches width x 26 inches height.

name: Irish Fairy Doll
description:
FREE SHIPPING WORLDWIDE

Spirits of the Forest

Our Irish Fairy Dolls are based on the Celtic Tree Zodiac and represent the spirits of the forest.

Trees were a central part of Celtic spirituality, so much so, the Celts designated a tree to each moon phase in accordance with its magical properties. There are 13 lunar months per year.

This Spirit Doll represents:

The Holly Tree - 11 July to 7 Aug 

Holly Tree = Practical
Holly Tree people are logical and efficient and have a good business sense......

Find out which tree the Celts chose for you at rathart.com

They bend in whatever shape you want them to be in and each Spirit Doll has its own special nest.


These Spirit dolls have been individually made to convey the character of the trees in the Ogham Tree Calendar.

They are made with wire, exquisite yarns and sparkling threads.
